Major News Items in Leading Indian Newspapers
NEW DELHI , November 30 ( Xinhua ) -- The following are major news items in leading Indian newspapers Monday .
The Hindustan Times :
-- The Congress party is set to move an adjournment motion in the Lower House of Parliament , which is scheduled to start its winter session from Monday , on the spiraling prices to expose the " fragility " of Atal Behari Vajpayee 's government on the issue .
The Times of India :
-- With the Congress performance in three states of Delhi , Madhya Pradesh and Rajasthan establishing her vote-winning potential , Congress President Sonia Gandhi has wrested the initiative from Prime Minister Vajpayee of Bharatiya Janata Party .
The Statesman :
-- The Left Front stopped short of demanding an outright resignation from the central government , but observed that it had " no moral right to continue " in view of a " clear verdict " in the Assembly polls .
The Economic Times :
-- Prime Minister Vajpayee said Sunday that the present volatility of Indian politics will have no fundamental impact on economic reforms in the country .
